brewery.brewery_description: A small independent quality focused brewery located both on the beach at Moffat Beach and a production facility and taproom in Caloundra West on the Sunshine Coast. Award wins include: Champion Medium Brewery (Indies 2023, 2022); Champion Queensland Brewery (Indies 2023, 2022, 2021); Champion Small Australian Brewery (AIBA 2023, 2022); Champion Small/Medium Brewery (QLD Beer Awards 2023, 2022); Champion Small/Medium Brewery (Indies 2021); Champion Brewpub (QLD Beer Awards 2021, 2020); Champion Brewpub (Indies 2020); Champion Small Brewery (Indies 2018).

beer.beer_name: Shadow of the Moon Strong Pale Ale
beer.beer_description:
The newest Aussie hop in HPA’s range is ECLIPSE. And just like that rare astronomical event, it always steals the show. With huge bursts of sweet mandarin, zesty citrus peel and a fresh pine needle bouquet. Join us as we dance in the shadow of the moon.

- 2023 Champion International-Style Pale Ale (AIBA)
- 2023 Gold Medal (AIBA)
- 2023 Gold Medal (QLD Beer Awards)
- 2022 Gold Medal (Indies)
- 2022 Champion International-Style Pale Ale (AIBA)
- 2022 Gold Medal (AIBA)
- 2021 Gold Medal (Indies)

Deep burnt red on the pour, heady aromas of candied orange and dried mango, resinous and warm on the palate. Snuggle up and hit reset.

- 2023 Gold Medal (AIBA)
- 2022 Gold Medal (Indies)
- 2022 Gold Medal (AIBA)
- 2019 Gold Medal (AIBA)
- 2019 Gold Medal (Indies)
- 2019 Silver Medal (QLD Beer Awards)

Tall, dark and mysterious, this handsome devil wants to lure you astray. Silky smooth tones of roast coffee and rich dark chocolate are bound to tempt. But be careful… there are a lot of spent oats in this character’s dark past. You might just have come across a cereal killa!

- 2022 Gold Medal (QLD Beer Awards)
- 2021 Bronze Medal (QLD Beer Awards)
- 2020 Silver Medal (Indies)
- 2019 Silver Medal (Indies)

During his time in the Army, our founder and head brewer Matt Wilson served in Recon Platoon 1RAR with a soldier named Josh Porter. Josh enlisted in 2000 and on completion of recruit training was posted to 1RAR where he became a qualified sniper. After completing his service in Recon Platoon, Josh went on to undertake special forces selection in 2004, and served with the SAS in East Timor, The Solomon Islands and Afghanistan. Very sadly, Josh was killed in a Blackhawk helicopter crash in November 2006. Josh is survived by his wife Carinna and his daughter Maddison who was unborn at the time of his death. In remembrance of Josh, we brewed a beer in his name. This is an American Style Strong Pale Ale that has a big malt backbone and a hefty dose of hops. Like Josh, this beer is smooth, robust, full flavoured and will always have your back.

- 2018 Silver Medal (AIBA)
- 2018 Bronze Medal (Indies)
- 2017 Silver Medal (Indies)

Heavily hopped with Amarillo, Mosaic, Citra, Galaxy and Comet, we’ve got the whole fruit salad here with big tropical aromas, a juicy haze, balanced by a smooth bitterness to bring it all home.

- 2021 Bronze Medal (AIBA)
- 2021 Bronze Medal (QLD Beer Awards)
- 2020 Champion IPA (QLD Beer Awards) 
- 2020 Gold Medal (QLD Beer Awards)
- 2020 Bronze Medal (Indies)
- 2019 Bronze Medal (AIBA)

Hops or malt? This beer balances the best of both. Specialty malts provoke burnt caramel, toffee and candy flavours whilst a huge hopping regime brings notes of citrus, pine and resin. All blending seamlessly to deliver a full-flavoured yet perfectly balanced beer made for the cooler months.
Collaboration West Coast IPA with Moffat Beach Brewery and Deep Creek.

With targets locked on flavour, we've loaded up on hops and fired everything we've got at this beast of a beer. It's a direct hit to the senses with explosions of luscious tropical fruit, a smooth bitterness to tease the palate, and a golden haze left in its wake. We found the flavour we were looking for. Now it's yours to enjoy.

- 2022 Silver Medal (Indies)

When ‘beer isn’t your thing’, we bet you’d like a Party Mix Sour. Tart, refreshing and incredibly easy to drink, this batch features a massive wallop of passionfruit to keep you on your toes.

- 2021 Bronze Medal (QLD Beer Awards)
- 2020 Bronze Medal (Indies)

Is it a Pale Ale? Is it an IPA? No, wait… Hazy Pale? One of the best things about beer is its evolution. And this cloudy curiosity is a crossover that takes in the best of the ale world. Don’t overthink it. And enjoy.
When ‘beer isn’t your thing’, we bet you’d like a Party Mix Sour. Tart, refreshing and incredibly easy to drink, this smashable boysenberry treat is laced with a hint of lactose for extra creaminess.

Our beer of the Summer. Brewed with pilsner malt, flaked corn and lager yeast, the finish is dry as a chip, and just begs for a refill. Against this lighter backdrop, we’ve painted a complex melange of new world hops provoking notes of citrus, tropical fruit, cannabis, papaya, and durian to hit you like a rogue breaker when your back’s turned. Now, that’s refreshing.

- 2023 Silver Medal (QLD Beer Awards)

beer.beer_name: 7 Inch Series: Nectaron Single Hop Pale Ale
beer.beer_description: Our 7 Inch series aims to showcase one hop varietal in all its glory. Nectaron is a New Zealand hop, lovingly crafted over 17 years, and provokes intense tropical fruit characters of pineapple and passionfruit, peach and citrus. Just perfect for an arvo Pale Ale by the beach.

Starring a pair of experimental hops out of Yakima Valley (so new they’re not even named yet), this super flavourful beer delivers big notes of ripe peach and apricot, nuanced by a sherbet tang and lingering sweetness.

Brewed in the shadow of a 5G tower in a tin-hat shaped fermenter at Area 51 (Caloundra Rd), this beer is not what it seems. Your eyes are screaming IPA, your taste buds are saying Stout, and your mind is slowly dissolving into the discord of madness. dO yOUr ReSeaRch! It’s all a LIE!
 
Brewed for GABS Craft Beer & Cider Festival 2022.
When ‘beer isn’t your thing’, we bet you’d like a Party Mix Sour. Tart, refreshing and incredibly easy to drink, this smashable raspberry delight is laced with a hint of lactose for extra creaminess.

A classic English ale, Hipsterdoofus is a malt-driven decadence of toffee, hazelnut and raisin. A touch of Fuggles and East Kent Goldings hops add a mild, earthy bitterness which allows the British malts to shine like a London pub on a rainy night.

- 2019 Bronze Medal (Indies)

When ‘beer isn’t your thing’, we bet you’d like a Party Mix Sour. Tart, refreshing and incredibly easy to drink, this summer sipper is jammed full of fresh raspberries and passionfruit for extra zing!

- 2022 Silver Medal (QLD Beer Awards)
